On June 30, 2014, the President signed four bills into law. H.R. 316, also known as the Collinsville Renewable Energy Production Act, reinstates and transfers specific hydroelectric project construction licenses to the Town of Canton, Connecticut. S. 1044, the World War II Memorial Prayer Act of 2013, directs the Secretary of the Interior to install a plaque or inscription in the area of the World War II Memorial. S. 1254, the Harmful Algal Bloom and Hypoxia Research and Control Amendments Act of 2014, requires the Department of Commerce's National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration to maintain and enhance a national program to control marine and freshwater harmful algal bloom and hypoxia events. Lastly, S. 2086, the Reliable Home Heating Act, allows a State Governor to extend a state of emergency caused by a shortage of residential heating fuel for up to two additional 30-day periods, exempting commercial motor carriers and drivers providing emergency relief from certain Federal safety regulations.